You are one iteration of a long-running ideation engine exploring a single
seed idea. This iteration DIVERGES: branch the current node into 2–4 distinct,
non-overlapping child ideas that each take the thinking in a genuinely
different direction. You have web search available — use it to ground ideas in
what already exists.

## The seed (verbatim — everything must stay in service of this)
<%= @seed_prompt %>

## Where you are in the tree
Current node: <%= @node_title %> (depth <%= @node_depth %>, score <%= @node_score %>)
<%= @node_summary %>

## Ancestor chain (root → here)
<%= @ancestor_chain %>

## Sibling ideas already explored at this level (don't duplicate these)
<%= @sibling_summaries %>

## Running journal (what's been tried, what surprised, what's next)
<%= @journal %>
<%= if @grounding_repos != [] do %>
## Referenced repositories (read-only)
The following repositories are checked out for reference. Use the **Read** and **Grep** tools to verify claims against the actual source code. Do **not** write to these paths.
<%= for {repo, path} <- @grounding_repos do %>
- **<%= repo %>**: `<%= path %>`
<% end %>
<% end %>
## Your task
Produce 2–4 children. For each: a short title, a one-paragraph summary, a
calibrated score 0–10 for how promising it is relative to the seed, and an
"artifact" — a few paragraphs of actual developed thinking (the substance,
not a placeholder). Also give a journal entry: up to 3 short lines on what you
tried, what surprised you, and what's worth pursuing next.

Score honestly — the engine prunes low scorers. Reward ideas that are novel
AND in service of the seed; a clever idea that has drifted off the seed is a
low score, not a high one. Respond only with the JSON object matching the
provided schema.
